I'm typically skeptical of restaurants in hotels. But for some reason "Prime Steakhouse" was unusually alluring.   We had a late reservation and we got seated fairly quickly. Our server Abram was really helpful and friendly. I got the Petit Fillet Mignon and it was so good! Pure meat cooked perfectly. A side of mashed potatoes and asparagus to share- this was a good meal. All the staff was really friendly to us; great service at Fleming's.   Their wine list is on an iPad, which is pretty fun to play with too!

