This was one awkward experience I wish I could forget. Everything about Axis-Radius is awkward. The space is awkward, the people are awkward, the dancing is awkward, even the DJ was awkwardly mixing the music.   Nothing about A-R could get me in the mood to get my dance on, not even a few drinks. I tried in the room with house music until unusually strong fog machines came blasting down on my body from above. Was I being abducted by aliens?! Why can't I see anything around me?? What's going on? That was my cue to leave. I was excited to check out the Scottsdale nightlife but I must have come to the wrong place.

